Defendant in custody.
On count 1, burglary, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seven (7) years. That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by four (4) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentences imposed in 14 CF 97 and 14 CF 156 and with the sentence presently being served in Kewaunee County.
On count 2, felony theft, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of four (4) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by two (2) years extended supervision, concurrent with count 1 of this case and with the sentences imposed in 14 CF 97 and 14 CF 156 and with the sentence presently being served in Kewaunee County.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Programs.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain fulltime employment;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) maintain absolute sobriety;
7) pay restitution of $85.00 to James Rahmlow;
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
Minutes.
